"WWC0013&#xa0;&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;&#xa0;\n&#xa0;&#xa0;\n&#xa0;&#xa0;\n&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;Research has shown that for children between the ages of seven to 16, \nthe involveme\nnt of parents\n \nin their schooling had a greater influence on attainment than family background, size of family and level of \nparental education\n. \nParental engagement with their child’s education can \nhave \na real impact on attainment\n,\n and a parent’s attitude to school, often based on their own experiences of education, can also significantly affect their child’s attitude\n and subsequent achievement\n. \n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;\nSeptember 2013\n The Centre for Social Justice, \nRequires Improvement: The Causes of Educational \nFailure\n (September 2013), p.14.\n Further information on the use of SGS in Wales, as well as the other examples of formative assessment use noted in this response, is available on request.\n"